{"id":19745,"date":"2020-02-22T02:03:54","date_gmt":"2020-02-22T01:03:54","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.saltinourhair.com\/?p=19745"},"modified":"2021-10-27T08:54:10","modified_gmt":"2021-10-27T07:54:10","slug":"koh-lipe","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.saltinourhair.com\/thailand\/koh-lipe\/","title":{"rendered":"Koh Lipe: A Guide to Thailand&#8217;s Paradise Island"},"content":{"rendered":"<div class=\"wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<h2 id=\"todo\">5 Things To Do in Koh Lipe<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Koh Lipe is far less crowded than other places like <a href=\"https:\/\/www.saltinourhair.com\/thailand\/krabi\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\"Krabi (opens in a new tab)\">Krabi<\/a>, or <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\"Bangkok (opens in a new tab)\" href=\"https:\/\/www.saltinourhair.com\/thailand\/things-to-do-bangkok\/\" target=\"_blank\">Bangkok<\/a>. It is not a party island and therefore attracts a different kind of tourist. The small tropical island can be explored within 30 minutes on a bicycle and is all about beaches. These are the things to do in Koh Lipe, Thailand.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><div class=\"image-wrapper\"><div class=\"fake-image\"><\/div><noscript><img src=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/02\/23123111\/best-things-to-do-koh-lipe-island.jpg\" alt=\"koh lipe island ultimate guide\"><\/noscript><img width=\"450\" height=\"300\" alt=\"koh lipe island ultimate guide\" class=\"wp-image-19764 lazypreload\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/02\/23123111\/best-things-to-do-koh-lipe-island.jpg 1920w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/02\/23123111\/best-things-to-do-koh-lipe-island-300x200.jpg 300w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/02\/23123111\/best-th